The board shall set the amount of the fees required to be paid by the applicants for licensure and the license holders including, but not limited to, the following:
For an application for initial licensure as a licensed professional art therapist, the fee shall be nonrefundable and shall not exceed two hundred dollars ($200);
For an application for initial licensure as a licensed professional art therapist associate, the fee shall be nonrefundable and shall not exceed one hundred dollars ($100);
To take an examination, the fee shall not exceed one hundred dollars ($100), or, if a national examination is used, the amount of the fee shall not exceed the cost of the examination by more than twenty-five percent (25%);
The renewal fee for a licensed professional art therapist shall not exceed two hundred dollars ($200);
The renewal fee for a licensed professional art therapist associate shall not exceed one hundred dollars ($100);
For a duplicate or replacement license, the fee shall not exceed twenty-five dollars ($25);
For failure to renew a license for a licensed professional art therapist within the allotted grace period pursuant to KRS 309.1335(3), the fee shall not exceed one hundred dollars ($100);
For failure to renew a license for a licensed professional art therapist associate within the allotted grace period pursuant to KRS 309.1335, the fee shall not exceed fifty dollars ($50); and
Other reasonable fees for administrative services.
